Note:
==============================================================================
Account - Banking and on-chain account identifiers
==============================================================================

Strongly-typed account identifier families:

  IBAN          ISO 13616 international bank account number
                Format: <2 country><2 check><BBAN up to 30>
                Validation: mod-97 check (must equal 1)

  ACHAccount    US ACH routing + account number
                Routing: 9 digits with ABA check digit (NACHA)

  SWIFTBIC      ISO 9362 business identifier code
                Format: 8 or 11 chars (AAAA BB CC [DDD])
                AAAA institution, BB country, CC location, DDD branch

  OnChainAddress  Parametric over Network type
                  ETH: 20-byte hex with EIP-55 mixed-case checksum
                  BTC: Base58Check P2PKH/P2SH (handled via base58 helper)

  LedgerAccount  Internal chart-of-accounts code

References:
  - ISO 13616-1:2020 Financial services - International bank account number (IBAN)
  - ISO 9362:2022 Banking - Banking telecommunication messages - BIC
  - NACHA Operating Rules and Guidelines, ACH routing number specification
  - EIP-55 Ethereum address checksum (Vitalik Buterin et al., 2016)
  - BIP-39/BIP-32 Bitcoin address conventions
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as MemoryCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/sha3.runa" as Sha3
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena

Note: ============================================================================
Note: IBAN
Note: ============================================================================

Constant IBAN_MIN_LENGTH as Integer is 15
Constant IBAN_MAX_LENGTH as Integer is 34

Constant IBAN_RECORD_SIZE as Integer is 56
Constant IBAN_FIELD_LENGTH as Integer is 0
Constant IBAN_FIELD_VALID as Integer is 8
Constant IBAN_FIELD_RAW_PTR as Integer is 16
Constant IBAN_FIELD_COUNTRY_CODE as Integer is 24
Constant IBAN_FIELD_CHECK_DIGITS as Integer is 32
Constant IBAN_FIELD_BBAN_OFFSET as Integer is 40
Constant IBAN_FIELD_BBAN_LENGTH as Integer is 48

Process called "iban_country_expected_length" takes country_code_packed as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the exact IBAN length mandated by the SWIFT IBAN Registry for
    the given ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. The country code is passed
    in packed form (first letter in the high byte, second in the low byte:
    (c0 << 8) | c1, e.g. 'DE' -> 0x4445 = 17477). Returns -1 for any
    country not in the registry, which the validator treats as a
    structural rejection.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Encodes the SWIFT IBAN Registry (verified as of 2024) as an explicit
    case ladder. Each arm carries the country's exact expected total
    length (country code + check digits + BBAN). All 77 registered
    countries are enumerated.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Branch-based dispatch. The packed-integer compare collapses both
    letters into one 64-bit equality test per arm.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure. Unknown country codes return -1; the caller must reject.
    @End Security_Scope

    Note: AD = (65<<8)|68 = 16708
    If country_code_packed is equal to 16708:
        Return 24
    End If
    Note: AE = (65<<8)|69 = 16709
    If country_code_packed is equal to 16709:
        Return 23
    End If
    Note: AL = (65<<8)|76 = 16716
    If country_code_packed is equal to 16716:
        Return 28
    End If
    Note: AT = (65<<8)|84 = 16724
    If country_code_packed is equal to 16724:
        Return 20
    End If
    Note: AZ = (65<<8)|90 = 16730
    If country_code_packed is equal to 16730:
        Return 28
    End If
    Note: BA = (66<<8)|65 = 16961
    If country_code_packed is equal to 16961:
        Return 20
